SIMPLE: moho
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moho
<hw>Mo"ho</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A gallinule (<spn>Notornis Mantelli</spn>)
formerly inhabiting New Zealand, but now supposed to be extinct. It was
incapable of flight. See <er>Notornis</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moho</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moho
<hw>Mo"ho</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Short for
<ets>Mohorovicic discontinuity</ets>, from <person>Andrija
<etsep>Mohorovi⟦ccar⟧i⟦cacute⟧</etsep></person>, a Yugoslavian
geologist.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The boundary between the
earth's crust and the semiliquid mantle beneath. It varies in depth from
3 miles beneath the surface at certain points in the ocean to over 25
miles under certain parts of continents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mohock</ent>⟦br⟧
